cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as intent detection and slot filling. It may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a neural network model for these tasks. Additionally, it could belong to cs.SD (Sound) as speech recognition is mentioned as an application of attention-based encoder-decoder models. Finally, it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the proposed model is a neural network.
